{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:36:14.500383+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: b380f34724dc91ab7dba9d211f3d13d63eb72ede)", "id": "lc_c5466a0b-6c79-48a1-9c05-20a0572e9e82"}, {"type": "text", "text": "from http.server import BaseHTTPRequestHandler, HTTPServer\n\nclass Handler(BaseHTTPRequestHandler):\n    def do_GET(self):\n        body = b'Demo app for local ZAP baseline testing.\\n'\n        self.send_response(200)\n        self.send_header('Content-Type', 'text/plain')\n        self.send_header('Content-Length', str(len(body)))\n        self.end_headers()\n        self.wfile.write(body)\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    HTTPServer(('127.0.0.1', 8080), Handler).serve_forever()\n", "id": "lc_f2e3e690-8804-49b1-ada1-53aaeeda96ba"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "af394606-f023-4b57-a47e-eab3a4827e87", "tool_call_id": "call_1c786a2a169c4717840675e8", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:36:29.155813+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have a complete understanding of the situation. Let me provide my thorough analysis and findings.\n\n---\n\n## Review Summary for Issue #5: \"Add baseline report summary\"\n\n### Current Repository State\n\nAfter examining all the relevant files, here's what I found:\n\n**1. `sample_data/zap_baseline.json`** — ✅ Exists and is well-formed\n```json\n{\n  \"site\": [\n    {\n      \"@name\": \"http://127.0.0.1:8080\",\n      \"alerts\": [\n        {\n          \"pluginid\": \"10020\",\n          \"alert\": \"Missing Anti-clickjacking Header\",\n          \"riskdesc\": \"Medium (High)\",\n          \"desc\": \"Sample baseline finding for local demo app.\"\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**2. `scripts/zap_json_to_markdown.py`** — ✅ Exists with correct logic\nThe script already reads the JSON file and generates a proper Markdown table with columns: Rule (pluginid), Alert, and Risk (riskdesc). It writes output to `reports/baseline_summary.md`.\n\n**3. `reports/baseline_summary.md`** — ❌ **Missing!** This is the file that needs to be created.\n\n### The Gap\n\nThe script `scripts/zap_json_to_markdown.py` is correctly implemented but has never been run. The output file `reports/baseline_summary.md` does not exist (the `reports/` directory only contains `.gitkeep`).\n\n### What Needs to Happen\n\nThe file `reports/baseline_summary.md` should be created with the following content (generated from the script logic applied to the sample data):\n\n```markdown\n# ZAP Baseline Summary\n\n| Rule | Alert | Risk |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| 10020 | Missing Anti-clickjacking Header | Medium (High) |\n```\n\n### Validation Check\n\nI verified that the existing `scripts/validate_repo.py` validation script checks for required files (`README.md`, `SECURITY.md`, `zap/baseline.conf`, `sample_data/zap_baseline.json`, `scripts/run_zap_baseline.sh`) and verifies that the